   <mods:abstract>Madison's motion of April 18, referred to Secretary for Foreign Affairs.
            Resolves that American Minister to France proceed to Madrid to assure Spain of American
            friendship and determination settle peaceably question of Mississippi navigation and
            enter into any necessary negotiations. Sec. for Foreign Affairs to make necessary
            arrangements and provide letter of credence for Minister to France and inform Gardoqui
            of change in method of negotiating with his Government.</mods:abstract>
